Description: What I thought was an article is actually an ad for a Kubernetes-like alternative called virtuoso. They have an ISO for doing an on-prem install, and ability to do a cloud deploy in AWS. Their target seems to be homelabs and small envs, and it looks early but pretty solid. It's a VM wrangler, so a bit different then K8s, but might be K8s compatible. The dashboards look very slick. Worth a look I'd say.
