URL reference: https://www.iqsource.ai/en/blog/kubernetes-playbook-ai-agents-payroll/
DateReviewed: 2026-05-04
Description: Today's article uses a weird title to try and convey something else - I thought it was about using AI on financial data with guards, but it is actually about a guy who built Azure's container service moving to a payroll company. We start with a bit of background on this hire, along with a bit of shade on how AI containers are the next greatest thing. Then we talk a bit about early Kubernetes approach, and how it integrated in things like RBAC and audit logs to add strong security, and how the hire helped with that. We do get in a bit to the weeds on the AI side, looking at AI agent intent, tool use and trust delegation and how they loosly map to what K8s did. They then pivot back to Workday, talking about its stats then how it is using Sana that it acquired and it's AI agents that help clients get the info they need. They talk about the risks and attack surface, and how to dial down both of these while still getting done what you need. Interesting piece.
BottomLine: Interesting piece talking about a person moving along with how to make AI both useful and under control
